<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="521" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d521">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">211.65/110</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 594</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-22">June 22, 1934</date>.<lb/>[Received July
                                    5.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform the
                                Department that during a conversation this morning with Mr. Suvich,
                                Undersecretary for Foreign Affairs, I asked how their study of the
                                extradition treaty was progressing. He said that they were making
                                headway and he hoped to be able to talk to me soon.<note n="20" xml:id="d521fn20">No report of any further reply from the
                                    Italian Government regarding these negotiations has been found
                                    in the Department files.</note></p>
                            <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Breckinridge
                                Long</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>